drop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fgt1665702927330.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fgt1665702927330.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fgt1665702927330.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fgt1665702927330\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Environment Considerations for DB2\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">When using the DB2 connector, you need to be aware of some limitations that the platform and operating environment impose.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__section_l32_kp3_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1238345e51\">Network Considerations</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__p_d48236e1_d48237e1_d48238e1\">Both the Uniface Server and DB2 network capabilities can\n        be used. The Uniface Server is used to connect Uniface to the connector, and the DB2 network\n        capabilities are used to communicate between the connector and the DB2 database.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__section_ork_lp3_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1238345e60\">System Parameters</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__p_d48242e1_d48243e1_d48244e1\">On Microsoft Windows, DB2 sets the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">LOCKTIMEOUT</code> database parameter to infinite by default, meaning that when\n        a deadlock situation occurs, Uniface will hang indefinitely, instead of returning status\n        code -11, as on other platforms or other databases. To avoid this situation, the\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">LOCKTIMEOUT</code> parameter should be given a realistic value, for example, 30\n        seconds.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__p_d48245e1_d48246e1_d48247e1\">On RS/6000, setting the shell variable\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">LC_NUMERIC</code> affects the connector behavior. The DB2 connector on RS/6000\n        requires the environmental variable <code class=\"ph codeph\">LC_NUMERIC</code>, which must be set as\n        follows to ensure correct numeric formatting:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__pre_hwq_4p3_3cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">LC_NUMERIC = en_US\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__note_mwq_4p3_3cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The environment variable\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">LC_NUMERIC</code> must be set to a valid value on RS/6000 systems. If not set,\n        it can cause the operating system to become unstable.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__section_cdk_sp3_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1238345e93\">Using DB2 for the Repository</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__p_d48251e1_d48252e1_d48253e1\">You can use DB2 to store Uniface system information.\n        However, this can result in delays whenever the connector encounters locked records, because\n        the connector waits until the lock is released.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__p_d48254e1_d48255e1_d48256e1\">When using DB2 as the Repository, ensure that database\n        has a 32 KB-page size. For an existing database, add a 32 KB-page tablespace with a 32\n        KB-page buffer pool.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fgt1665702927330__p_d48257e1_d48258e1_d48259e1\">You should check the maximum number of open cursors\n        allowed on your system, because this can diminish performance if you use it to store Uniface\n        system information.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Environment Considerations for DB2 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Environment Considerations for DB2 When using the DB2 connector, you need to be aware of some limitations that the platform and operating environment impose. Network Considerations Both the Uniface Server and DB2 network capabilities can be used. The Uniface Server is used to connect Uniface to the connector, and the DB2 network capabilities are used to communicate between the connector and the DB2 database. System Parameters On Microsoft Windows, DB2 sets the LOCKTIMEOUT database parameter to infinite by default, meaning that when a deadlock situation occurs, Uniface will hang indefinitely, instead of returning status code -11, as on other platforms or other databases. To avoid this situation, the LOCKTIMEOUT parameter should be given a realistic value, for example, 30 seconds. On RS/6000, setting the shell variable LC_NUMERIC affects the connector behavior. The DB2 connector on RS/6000 requires the environmental variable LC_NUMERIC , which must be set as follows to ensure correct numeric formatting: LC_NUMERIC = en_US Copy CAUTION: The environment variable LC_NUMERIC must be set to a valid value on RS/6000 systems. If not set, it can cause the operating system to become unstable. Using DB2 for the Repository You can use DB2 to store Uniface system information. However, this can result in delays whenever the connector encounters locked records, because the connector waits until the lock is released. When using DB2 as the Repository, ensure that database has a 32 KB-page size. For an existing database, add a 32 KB-page tablespace with a 32 KB-page buffer pool. You should check the maximum number of open cursors allowed on your system, because this can diminish performance if you use it to store Uniface system information. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}